{"type":"message","id":"c3a72248","parentId":"64d6be92","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:00:05.116Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:b9110520-e052-4b6e-a8cf-3112bb46e172 auto-dream] # Dream: Memory Consolidation\n\nYou are performing a dream — a reflective pass over your memory files. Synthesize what you've learned recently into durable, well-organized memories so that future sessions can orient quickly.\n\nMemory directory: ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/\nMain memory: ~/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md\n\n## Phase 1 — Orient\n\n- Read MEMORY.md to understand the current long-term memory state\n- List memory/ directory to see daily files and evaluations\n- Read the last 2-3 days of memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md files\n- Read memory/dream-log.json for last dream results\n- Read memory/lessons.json if it exists\n\n## Phase 2 — Gather Recent Signal\n\nLook for new information worth persisting from the last 48h:\n1. New decisions, discoveries, events from daily files\n2. Task quality patterns from memory/evaluations/\n3. Contradictions — facts in MEMORY.md that conflict with recent activity\n4. Stale entries — references to completed/cancelled projects\n\nFocus on SIGNAL, not noise.\n\n## Phase 3 — Consolidate\n\nFor each thing worth remembering:\n- If it updates existing MEMORY.md content → edit in place\n- If it's new long-term knowledge → add to appropriate section\n- If it contradicts existing memory → fix the old entry\n- Convert ALL relative dates to absolute (\"yesterday\" → actual date)\n- Merge duplicate entries\n\nAlso check if memory/lessons.json has patterns from evaluations that should be promoted.\n\n## Phase 4 — Prune and Index\n\nMEMORY.md maintenance:\n- Remove entries about completed/cancelled projects (unless lesson is universal)\n- Remove outdated info (stale URLs, old infrastructure details)\n- Keep under 200 lines — if over, prune least-referenced entries\n- Ensure all sections are current and accurate\n\nDaily files older than 90 days: move to memory/archive/YYYY-MM/\n\n## Phase 5 — Log\n\nRead current memory/dream-log.json, then append your results:\n- What was added/updated/removed\n- MEMORY.md line count before and after\n- Files archived count\n- Set notable=true if significant changes were made\n- Keep only last 30 entries in the log\n- Write updated dream-log.json\n\nReturn a brief summary of what you consolidated, updated, or pruned. If nothing changed, say so.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, April 7th, 2026 — 3:00 AM (UTC) / 2026-04-07 03:00 UTC\n\nReturn your summary as plain text; it will be delivered automatically. If the task explicitly calls for messaging a specific external recipient, note who/where it should go instead of sending it yourself."}],"timestamp":1775530805079}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5d39a9a","parentId":"c3a72248","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:00:10.296Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI'll perform the dream consolidation. Let me start by reading all the relevant files."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_XUpSHB5qipP5FPyWBXa1iw","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_RcgTEv66IHrrBwvV0pfTF9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/ 2>/dev/null && echo \"---\" && ls -la /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/evaluations/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"no evaluations dir\""}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":3,"output":179,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":24397,"totalTokens":24579,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.004475,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.15248125,"total":0.15697125}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775530805111}}
{"type":"message","id":"3eb5398a","parentId":"f5d39a9a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:00:10.360Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_XUpSHB5qipP5FPyWBXa1iw","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md — Michael's Long-Term Memory\n> Last consolidated: 2026-04-06 03:00 UTC (auto-dream)\n\n## Who Lucy Is\n- SaaS Founder & PM at Sentra Technology, Indonesia, UTC+8 (WITA)\n- 10+ years IT/Project Management, managed $900K+ projects\n- Building DataFlow: AI OCR + accounting integration for Indonesian bookkeepers\n- Also manages Sentra Technology projects (B2B IT: FMS, HRIS, CCTV, POS)\n- **Values:** Speed > perfection, action > analysis, no sugarcoat, realistic timelines\n- **Style:** Hands-on but trusting, early morning messages = urgent, decisive\n- **Communication:** Shorter answers preferred. Less AI-sounding. Answer the core thing. Be natural, talk like a friend. Less is more. (Set 2026-03-27, reinforced 2026-03-30)\n\n## DataFlow Mission\n- Target: Indonesian bookkeepers (500K+ potential TAM)\n- Problem: Manual invoice/receipt entry + bookkeeping is painful\n- Solution: AI OCR (95%+ accuracy) + auto-accounting integration\n- Timeline: Originally April 5, 2026 (assessed unrealistic on Mar 8). Realistically June 30.\n- Revenue target Year 1: $250K, 250 customers\n- **30-Day Sprint (Mar 8 – Apr 5):** Sprint ended Apr 5 with zero bookkeeper validation completed. Focus shifted entirely to infrastructure, MAGI rebuild, and Sentra work. Gabriel & Raguel haven't done real outreach. DataFlow validation still pending — timeline TBD.\n\n## The Council (10 Deployed ✅)\n| Agent | Role | Superpower |\n|-------|------|-----------|\n| 🛡️ Michael | Wise Advisor | Risk/wisdom, enable bold moves, orchestrate sub-agents |\n| 🧭 Rafael | The Architect | Strategy, Fork/Synthesize, has own Telegram bot |\n| 🔥 Uriel | The Validator | Verify before speaking, proposes tests, dev work |\n| 📣 Gabriel | The Voice | Communication, brand, bookkeeper pitch |\n| 🤝 Raguel | The Friend | Relationships, recruitment, testimonials |\n| ⚖️ Samael | System Guardian | Finds contradictions + external threats |\n| 🔮 Sarael | The Scribe | Synthesis-only, structured analysis |\n| 💸 Azrael | The Auditor | ROI, costs, runway, Bedrock spend |\n| 🛡️ Remiel | The Sentry | UU PDP, KBLI, ISO, mining tender compliance |\n| 🛠️ Zadkiel | The Builder | Minimalist UX, mobile-first, quality gates |\n\nAll agents dispatchable as sub-agents. Parallel dispatch works (up to 4 concurrent).\n\n## Infrastructure\n- **VPS:** DigitalOcean Singapore, 8GB/4vCPU/160GB, Ubuntu 24.04, $48/month\n- **Credits:** ~$130 remaining from $200 DO credit (as of Apr 4). ~2.7 months runway at $48/mo.\n- **AI:** Claude Sonnet 4.6 via AWS Bedrock (us-west-2). $3/$15 per 1M input/output tokens.\n- **OpenClaw:** Running on VPS, gateway manages WhatsApp + Telegram\n- **MAGI:** https://magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io (⚠️ NEVER use /council path — deprecated)\n- **Paul Simulator (D&D):** https://64-227-110-70.sslip.io/dnd (PIN auth, full 2024 rules, Indonesian translations)\n- **Backend:** Node.js + Fastify at 127.0.0.1:3001, direct Bedrock API\n- **CouchDB/Obsidian LiveSync:** Docker port 5984, DB: obsidian-council\n- **PM2:** systemd service (`pm2-openclaw`), auto-resurrects council-room backend\n- **Voice:** STT via Whisper (local, CPU), TTS via Edge TTS (free). Both work on WhatsApp.\n- **WhatsApp:** Recurring gateway flapping issue (60s disconnect/reconnect cycles). Not blocking messages but burns resources. Root cause: creds.json corruption/race condition.\n\n## Skills & Capabilities (Built/Absorbed)\n**Core pipeline (Apr 4):** ULTRAPLAN → Pipeline Orchestrator → Auto-Dream (think → execute → learn)\n- pipeline-orchestrator: 5-stage (plan→prd→exec→verify→fix), parallel sub-agents, resumable\n- hierarchical-memory: 4-level DIKW, hot/warm/cold tiers, auto-promotion\n- auto-dream: nightly memory consolidation (this job)\n- ULTRAPLAN: 30-min deep planning with Opus\n\n**Absorbed skills (Mar 30):** twitter-reader, youtube-transcript, reddit-reader, github-enhanced, web-reader, exa-search, linkedin-reader, bilibili-reader, xiaohongshu-reader, systematic-debugging, dev-workflow, domain-intel, code-review\n\n**Other:** skill-absorber, autoskills, secret-scanner (TruffleHog, always --no-verification), self-improving, ontology, file-editor, visual-explainer, ui-ux-pro-max\n\n## MAGI v2 Features\n- Chat, Roundtable (turn-based, persists to disk), Mission Control, Analytics, Files, Settings\n- IT Support page (emergency controls, model management, diagnostics, quick commands with code blocks)\n- WhatsApp Allowlist Manager, Message Forwarding Rules\n- Personal Knowledge Base (/magi2/knowledge/)\n- Mini Roundtable (on-demand/scheduled/smart trigger)\n- Voice Call page (WebSocket, hold-to-talk, agent selector)\n- **User Management** (/users/): register flow, admin approve/reject, roles (Admin/User), admin-only endpoint protection\n- **Design System (Apr 5):** AlphaClaw Apex-inspired — JetBrains Mono, cyan #63ebff, grid texture, page transitions, stagger animations. D&D pages use amber #d4a73a.\n- **Full Redesign (Apr 5):** ~25 pages overhauled via 2x ULTRAPLAN + 8 parallel sub-agents. Shared infra extracted (core.css, components.css, core.js, nav.js, ws-manager.js). XSS fixed, memory leaks patched.\n- Login: lucy/magi2026 (NOT lucy2026 — that was Council Room legacy)\n- Registered users: Kenny (approved, user role), Adam & Rusdi (invited)\n\n## Active Projects\n\n### Kopilima Digital Core (SNC-K5)\n- **Client:** Kopilima cafe chain (10 branches)\n- **Vendor:** Sentra Technology — Lucy = PM\n- **Scope:** Custom POS + ERP replacing Majoo\n- **Pillars:** K.I.S.S + Anti-Fraud Sovereignty\n- **Key Modules:** POS (Hero Buttons), Ghost Guard (anti-fraud), Midnight Protocol (inventory), Agile HCM (payroll), Event/Membership, QR Pre-Order\n- **Blueprint:** knowledge-base/kopilima-snc-k5-blueprint.md\n\n### Sentra Brochure (Apr 1)\n- Product catalog/brosur in Canva for B2B sales\n- Products: FMS, Custom Apps, HRIS, AI CCTV, Smart Lock, SentrAI, Starlink, Telematics\n- Lucy writes in Canva, Michael provides copy\n\n### Claude Code Leak Archive (Apr 4)\n- 3 repos archived in ~/knowledge-base/ (leaked source, not model weights)\n- Key patterns extracted: autoDream, KAIROS, ULTRAPLAN, Buddy/Tamagotchi, 44 feature flags\n\n## Pending / Blocked\n- **Gmail login (deadboidump@gmail.com):** Google 2FA blocks headless VPS login. Waiting Lucy to choose alt verification. Creds saved at ~/.credentials/gmail.json\n- **WhatsApp flapping:** ~60s disconnect/reconnect cycles, ongoing since Apr 4. Messages still deliver. Needs re-link from Lucy's phone.\n- **Sentra WA Group:** Gateway added to g-notes-sentra but tag detection not working\n- **Richard account:** Lucy asked to delete \"richard\" MAGI account (Apr 5) — pending clarification on delete vs rename vs remove from protected list\n\n## Contact Book\n| Number | Name | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| +6285133221170 | Lucy (Richard) | The boss |\n| +6285845730981 | Rusdi | (was labeled Mr Salbi) |\n| +6285161502503 | Kenny | |\n| +6285159322166 | Paul | D&D player |\n| +6281345985715 | Ceka | |\n| +6282353412467 | Adam | Has MAGI access |\n| +6281938953639 | OpenClaw WA | Gateway number |\n\n## Behavioral Rules\n- See `memory/rules.md` for full always/never/when directives\n- \"1+1 = Bahlil\" = secret code for new contacts\n- Always confirm access requests with Lucy directly\n- Never share /council URL\n- Always --no-verification with TruffleHog\n\n## ICat Sales Context\n- Target: bisnis swasta lokal Kaltim (bukan franchise/BUMN besar)\n- SPBU = high-value target: CCTV + POS, deal Rp 15-40 juta/SPBU\n- Cold approach via WA hanya untuk swasta — pemerintah/BUMN = jalur formal\n\n## Resources Library\n| Resource | URL | Use Case |\n|---|---|---|\n| awesome-design-md | github.com/VoltAgent/awesome-design-md | 55 DESIGN.md files, cloned to knowledge-base/ |\n| ai-engineering-hub | github.com/patchy631/ai-engineering-hub | 93 AI projects: RAG, Agents, OCR |\n| public-apis | github.com/public-apis/public-apis | Free API collection |\n| Outscraper | outscraper.com | GMaps scraping $0.4/1K |\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775530810357}}
