{"type":"message","id":"2354ebe6","parentId":"c097969c","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:00:15.091Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_cDksg5jjY1rXQhumcdKvoT","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-06.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_XVll43KAipcKoBrn9kIRf8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-05.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_vnzeSTahCos0V5xQOlvCVi","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-04.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_qb0SzNH1sCULoqeEcGybDx","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/dream-log.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_zFm8ArNP8opb183g0HDXiJ","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/lessons.json"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_wW9qRTFLodSSlCFNpK7HA5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/rules.md"}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":328,"cacheRead":24397,"cacheWrite":4173,"totalTokens":28899,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0082,"cacheRead":0.0121985,"cacheWrite":0.02608125,"total":0.04648475}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775530810366}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3b9f4e0","parentId":"2354ebe6","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:00:15.152Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_cDksg5jjY1rXQhumcdKvoT","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-06 — Massive Build Day\n\n## GitHub Skills Upload\n- 35 skill repos created and pushed to github.com/Icattj\n- All public, MIT licensed, topics: openclaw, ai-agent, agent-skill, llm\n- Author: icattj\n- bilibili-reader and xiaohongshu-reader deleted (Chinese-specific, not needed)\n- Total GitHub repos now: 38 (35 skills + pompy + gmaps + icat)\n\n## Pangkas — Barbershop POS App\n- Built from Rome Bois as base (proven UI)\n- Added: Onboarding wizard, Home dashboard, Antrian/Queue, WA reminders, configurable shop name\n- Live at: https://64-227-110-70.sslip.io/pangkas/\n- GitHub: github.com/Icattj/pangkas\n- v1.1: 2435 lines single-file index.html\n- Decision: \"Pangkas\" = product name, shop name configurable in settings\n\n## Deep Think System Upgrade\n- Connected WhatsApp → MAGI Deep Think API (real multi-agent debate)\n- Script: ~/bin/magi-deep-think.py triggers MAGI API\n- Script: ~/bin/push-deep-think.py writes directly to data file\n- Upgraded to intensity 10 (max depth) always\n- Added multi-round debate (1-7 rounds, slider in UI)\n- Each round has specific purpose: debate → counter-debate → final positions → deep dive → convergence\n- Rounds parameter working (confirmed in data)\n\n## MAGI Fixes\n- Fixed ? help button (was broken due to module scope issue)\n- Added standalone script for help toggle (global scope, not module)\n- Fixed CSS: help panel z-index 9999, hardcoded positioning (--topbar-height was undefined)\n- Added agent profiles to help panel (fetched from API, grouped by layer)\n- Added rounds slider to Deep Think page\n\n## Deep Think Results Saved\n- \"Pangkas — Barbershop App Rebrand & Feature Plan\"\n- \"Website Builder System\" (3 agents)\n- \"Website Builder & Portfolio Showcase — FULL ARCHITECTURE\" (3 agents)\n- \"test rounds parameter\" (rounds=1, working)\n\n## Pending\n- Website Builder app (wireframe received, deep think done, needs build)\n- Skill repos need rename from openclaw-skill-* to proper branded names\n- MAGI pages, DnD, Council Room still need GitHub upload\n- QA checklist script (promised but not built yet)\n- Lucy wants MAGI to not be \"general ChatGPT\" — focus on specialized tools\n- Richard account MAGI deletion still pending\n\n## Lucy Feedback\n- \"Pangkas looks like website built by SMP student\" → rebuilt from Rome Bois base\n- \"? button doesn't work\" → fixed after multiple attempts\n- \"How can you be QA but miss things\" → committed to pre-delivery testing\n- Prefers Rome Bois visual style over generic builds\n- Wants Deep Think slider for rounds\n- Wants agent descriptions in help panel\n\n## Session Progress (continued)\n\n### GitHub Skills Upload\n- 35 skill repos uploaded to Icattj account (all public, MIT license)\n- 2 Chinese skills removed (bilibili, xiaohongshu)  \n- Author changed to \"icattj\"\n- 2 repos still pending: council-comms, reddit\n\n### Pangkas Barbershop App\n- Rome Bois → Pangkas rebrand\n- v1.0: Full rebuild attempted (multi-file, then single-file) — both had issues\n- v1.1: Rome Bois base + upgrades (onboarding, antrian, home dashboard, WA reminder, configurable shop name)\n- Live at /pangkas/ on VPS\n- GitHub: Icattj/pangkas\n\n### MAGI Deep Think Upgrades\n- Connected WhatsApp → MAGI Deep Think API (real multi-agent debate)\n- push-deep-think.py for direct file saves\n- magi-deep-think.py for API-triggered debates\n- Intensity forced to 10 (max) for all Deep Think sessions\n- Multi-round debate (1-7 rounds, configurable via slider)\n- Each round has unique instruction (debate → counter-debate → final positions → convergence)\n- Rounds slider added to MAGI Deep Think frontend\n- Synthesis prompt upgraded (7 sections including Technical Architecture + Timeline)\n\n### MAGI Chat Fixes  \n- ? Help button fixed (was broken due to module scope issue)\n- Added standalone global script for help toggle\n- Help panel now shows all 12 agents with roles, descriptions, color-coded by layer\n- Features list in Indonesian\n- z-index and CSS variable issues fixed\n\n### Deep Think → ULTRAPLAN renamed to Deep Think\n- Same functionality, integrated with MAGI branding\n\n### Planned: Website Builder\n- Wireframe received from Lucy (split-panel: code editor + live preview)\n- Deep Think triggered for architecture planning\n- Concept: portfolio showcase + code playground for Sentra Technology\n# 2026-04-06 — Massive Build Day\n\n## GitHub Skills Upload\n- 35 skill repos created and pushed to github.com/Icattj\n- All public, MIT licensed, topics: openclaw, ai-agent, agent-skill, llm\n- Author: icattj\n- bilibili-reader and xiaohongshu-reader deleted (Chinese-specific, not needed)\n- Total GitHub repos now: 38 (35 skills + pompy + gmaps + icat)\n\n## Pangkas — Barbershop POS App\n- Built from Rome Bois as base (proven UI)\n- Added: Onboarding wizard, Home dashboard, Antrian/Queue, WA reminders, configurable shop name\n- Live at: https://64-227-110-70.sslip.io/pangkas/\n- GitHub: github.com/Icattj/pangkas\n- v1.1: 2435 lines single-file index.html\n- Decision: \"Pangkas\" = product name, shop name configurable in settings\n- First multi-file attempt failed (3 agents built incompatible code — CSS mismatch, routing disconnect)\n- Second single-file rebuild also failed (timed out, looked too generic per Lucy)\n- Final approach: copy Rome Bois base + surgically add features = success\n\n## Deep Think System Upgrade\n- Connected WhatsApp → MAGI Deep Think API (real multi-agent debate)\n- Script: ~/bin/magi-deep-think.py triggers MAGI API\n- Script: ~/bin/push-deep-think.py writes directly to data file\n- Upgraded to intensity 10 (max depth) always\n- Added multi-round debate (1-7 rounds, slider in UI)\n- Each round has specific purpose: debate → counter-debate → final positions → deep dive → convergence\n- Rounds parameter confirmed working in backend + frontend\n- ULTRAPLAN renamed to Deep Think (aligned with MAGI branding)\n- Deep Think from WA now triggers real MAGI multi-agent debate (not cloned sub-agents)\n\n## MAGI Fixes\n- Fixed ? help button (broken due to module scope — onclick couldn't reach module functions)\n- Solution: standalone global script BEFORE module script, sets window.toggleHelp\n- Fixed CSS: help panel z-index 9999, hardcoded positioning (--topbar-height was undefined)\n- Added agent profiles to help panel (fetched from /api/agents, grouped by layer)\n- Added rounds slider to Deep Think page\n- Fixed Deep Think history click handler (same module scope issue — added fallback global handler)\n- Deep Think detail view: fallback renders raw text if module handler fails\n- MAGI Chat page briefly showed white/unstyled — cache issue, resolved with hard refresh\n\n## Deep Think Results Stored\n- \"Pangkas — Barbershop App Rebrand & Feature Plan\" (from Pangkas rebuild)\n- \"Website Builder System\" (3 agents: rafael, uriel, zadkiel)\n- \"Website Builder & Portfolio Showcase — FULL ARCHITECTURE\" (3 agents, intensity 10)\n- \"Rombak Web Pangkas\" (3 agents, 3 rounds, intensity 10 — 26K char synthesis)\n- \"test rounds parameter\" (rounds=1, verification)\n\n## Recurring Issues & Lessons\n- **Module scope vs inline onclick**: MAGI uses `<script type=\"module\">` but inline `onclick=\"fn()\"` can't see module-scoped functions. window.fn assignment helps but if module errors before the assignment, button is dead. Fix: add standalone <script> as fallback BEFORE module.\n- **Sub-agent timeouts on large files**: Single sub-agent can't write 2000+ line files — times out. Fix: use Rome Bois copy+modify approach for large files, or split into smaller sub-agents per component.\n- **Lucy feedback on quality**: \"looks like SMP student website\" — agents generating code default to safe/generic. Real quality = copy proven design (Rome Bois) and modify. Don't generate from scratch.\n- **Gateway timeout**: Session context grew too large after hours of chat → LLM timeout. Fixed: raised timeoutSeconds 600→3600.\n- **Always test before saying \"done\"**: Committed to QA checklist (not yet built as script).\n\n## GitHub Token\n- New fine-grained PAT stored in ~/.credentials/github-token and ~/.git-credentials\n- Scopes: repo create, push, delete\n- Account: Icattj\n\n## Pending Items\n- Website Builder app build (wireframe + deep think done, needs execution)\n- 33 skill repos need rename from openclaw-skill-* to proper branded names\n- MAGI pages, DnD, Council Room need GitHub upload (queued for daily commits)\n- QA script for web testing (promised, not yet built)\n- Deep Think detail view fix needs verification from Lucy\n- MAGI Chat page white-flash issue needs root cause investigation\n- Rome Bois path: ~/council-room/frontend/romebois/ (keep as legacy)\n\n## Configuration Changes\n- OpenClaw gateway timeout: 600s → 3600s (in /home/openclaw/.openclaw/config.yaml)\n- MAGI Deep Think: hardcoded intensity 10 (DEEP_INTENSITY constant in server.js)\n- MAGI Deep Think: multi-round loop at line ~2383 in server.js\n- Deep thinks data file: ~/magi-v2/backend/data/deep-thinks.json\n\n## Evening Session Progress\n\n### Skill Repos Renamed ✅\n- All 33 repos renamed from openclaw-skill-* to clean names\n- e.g., openclaw-skill-auto-dream → auto-dream\n\n### Security Hardening ✅\n- CouchDB: 0.0.0.0 → 127.0.0.1 (Docker rebind)\n- Sentra AI: 0.0.0.0 → 127.0.0.1\n- Crucix: 0.0.0.0 → 127.0.0.1  \n- DnD backend: 0.0.0.0 → 127.0.0.1\n- Only SSH (22/2222), Caddy (80/443), OpenClaw (18789) exposed\n\n### Cleanup ✅\n- Deleted: hermes-agent, openspace, claude-code (3), GitVizz\n- Kept: career-ops (Lucy wants for job search)\n\n### New Installations ✅\n- 5 Obsidian skills (defuddle, json-canvas, bases, cli, markdown)\n- 58 design systems → Obsidian vault\n- Camoufox anti-detect browser + GMaps scraper skill\n- Crucix OSINT dashboard (29 sources, live)\n- get-shit-done spec-driven dev cloned\n- qmd installed (needs local LLM, deferred)\n\n### Repo Audit Deep Think ✅\n- 4 agents evaluated all 27 repos\n- 6 IMPLEMENT NOW, 6 LATER, 6 REFERENCE, 7 DELETE\n- New rule: every repo must answer 4 questions before clone\n\n### Building (in progress)\n- Pangkas v2 (bottom nav + polish) — sub-agent running\n- Website Builder — sub-agent running\n- GitNexus — needs TypeScript build, deferred to P2\n\n## Late Night Final Push\n\n### Pangkas v1.3 ✅\n- Discount chips (None/10%/20%/50%/Custom)\n- \"Seperti Biasa\" quick reorder button\n- Bar chart 7-day revenue in Laporan\n- Bottom nav (from v1.2)\n\n### 33 Skill READMEs Updated ✅\n- All 33 skill repos now have proper README.md (not just SKILL.md copy)\n\n### GMaps Scraper Fixed ✅\n- Returned 10 barbershops in Balikpapan\n- Camoufox-based, anti-detect\n\n### qmd Local Search ✅\n- Indexed 164 Obsidian vault files\n- BM25 search working (no embeddings needed)\n- Collection: vault → /home/openclaw/livesync-bridge/vault\n\n### Shannon Security Setup\n- Configured to use Sentra AI as backend proxy\n- Docker image pulling for scan\n\n### GitNexus: SKIPPED\n- Too many dependency issues (React + Vite + TypeScript chain)\n- Keep as reference only\n\n### Final GitHub Count: 42 repos\n- 33 skill repos (clean names, proper README)\n- pangkas, sentra-ai, sentra-builder, magi, council-room, dnd-companion\n- 3 legacy (pompy, gmaps, icat)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775530815151}}
{"type":"message","id":"fcd90d08","parentId":"f3b9f4e0","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:00:15.156Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_XVll43KAipcKoBrn9kIRf8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-05\n\n## 04:00-06:00 — Code-Blocks Integration + Rusdi Song Analysis\n- Integrated pheralb/code-blocks into IT Support page (Sugar-High syntax highlighter, copy buttons, language badges, line numbers)\n- Added Quick Commands card (OpenClaw, PM2, System, Docker)\n- Analyzed Ringo Biyori (Spice & Wolf ED1) and Ringo to Kimi (ED2 2024 remake) in deep detail for Rusdi\n\n## 06:00-06:15 — ULTRAPLAN #1: MAGI Redesign\n- Lucy requested full MAGI web app redesign with zero bugs\n- ULTRAPLAN Opus session analyzed all 18 pages + backend + Caddy\n- Found: no auth enforcement, XSS in roundtable, memory leaks, ~600 lines duplicated, 5 different CSS variable sets\n- Decision: Vanilla ES Modules (no build tools) — extract shared infrastructure\n\n## 06:15-06:30 — AlphaClaw Discovery\n- Lucy shared https://github.com/chrysb/alphaclaw — OpenClaw setup harness\n- Also shared AlphaClaw Apex tweet (native Mac app for fleet management)\n- Extracted video frames (65s demo) — analyzed full UI/UX design language\n\n## 07:45-08:20 — MAGI Migration Wave 1 (4 parallel agents)\n- Agent 1: Shared infra (core.css, components.css, core.js, nav.js, ws-manager.js, markdown.js)\n- Agent 2: 4 core pages (chat, vault, roundtable, knowledge) — auth guard, shared markdown, XSS fix\n- Agent 3: 6 ops pages (settings, monitor, analytics, tasks, files, mission) — memory leak fixes\n- Agent 4: 8 biz pages (dashboard, login, leads, icat, pipeline, broadcast, notifications, reports)\nALL COMPLETED ✅\n\n## 08:45-09:30 — ULTRAPLAN #2 + APEX Visual Overhaul (4 parallel agents)\n- Lucy sent AlphaClaw Apex video, wants that UI/UX style\n- ULTRAPLAN #2: full visual redesign spec (Apex tokens, transitions, stagger animations)\n- Agent 1: Shared infra overhaul (cyan accent, JetBrains Mono, grid texture, transitions.js, countup.js)\n- Agent 2: Landing page complete redesign + core pages (stats, activity feed, quick actions)\n- Agent 3: 14 ops+business pages (color swap, stagger-item, data-countup, transitions)\n- Agent 4: Legacy pages (IT Support, Voice Call, Admin) + DnD app (amber accent)\nALL COMPLETED ✅ — ~25 pages overhauled\n\n## 09:30-10:00 — Bug Fixes\n- Bug 1: Hamburger nav not working — roundtable had own hamburger at higher z-index, fixed\n- Bug 2: Guide/? buttons in Chat — likely browser cache, code verified correct\n- Bug 3: Vault graph nodes unnamed — labels had opacity:0, changed to 0.7 + text shadow\n- Added body.has-nav padding-left for universal sidebar spacing\n\n## 10:00-10:30 — User Management System\n- Built register flow (login page → \"Request Access\")\n- Built /users/ admin page (approve/reject, role management, delete users)\n- Backend: /api/auth/register, /api/admin/users, approve, reject, role change, delete\n- Fixed API path bug (api('/admin/users') → api('admin/users'))\n- Fixed double JSON.stringify bug in approve/reject calls\n- Simplified roles: Admin + User only (was admin/editor/viewer)\n- Admin-only protection on: models, intensity, provider, routing, memory endpoints\n- Kenny registered & approved as user\n- Updated auth.json: guest & Kenny → \"user\" role\n- Core accounts (lucy, richard) = protected, can't be deleted\n\n## 10:30 — Notifications Sent\n- Adam: sign up for MAGI + notify Richard\n- Rusdi: sign up for MAGI + notify Richard  \n- Kenny: already registered, just login\n\n## 12:20 — Analyzed Phantom Sage \"Away\" for Rusdi\n\n## Standing Notes\n- WA gateway STILL flapping (~60s cycles, all day). Messages deliver fine. Lucy aware.\n- MAGI login: lucy/magi2026 or richard/magi2026 (NOT lucy2026, that's Council Room)\n- MAGI v2 backend restarted twice today (for new API routes)\n# 2026-04-05\n\n## 04:00-06:00 — Code-Blocks Integration + Rusdi Song Analysis\n- Integrated pheralb/code-blocks into IT Support page (Sugar-High syntax highlighter, copy buttons, language badges, line numbers)\n- Added Quick Commands card (OpenClaw, PM2, System, Docker)\n- Analyzed Ringo Biyori (Spice & Wolf ED1) and Ringo to Kimi (ED2 2024 remake) in deep detail for Rusdi\n\n## 06:00-06:15 — ULTRAPLAN #1: MAGI Redesign\n- Lucy requested full MAGI web app redesign with zero bugs\n- ULTRAPLAN Opus session analyzed all 18 pages + backend + Caddy\n- Found: no auth enforcement, XSS in roundtable, memory leaks, ~600 lines duplicated, 5 different CSS variable sets\n- Decision: Vanilla ES Modules (no build tools) — extract shared infrastructure\n\n## 06:15-06:30 — AlphaClaw Discovery\n- Lucy shared https://github.com/chrysb/alphaclaw — OpenClaw setup harness\n- Also shared AlphaClaw Apex tweet (native Mac app for fleet management)\n- Extracted video frames (65s demo) — analyzed full UI/UX design language\n\n## 07:45-08:20 — MAGI Migration Wave 1 (4 parallel agents)\n- Agent 1: Shared infra (core.css, components.css, core.js, nav.js, ws-manager.js, markdown.js)\n- Agent 2: 4 core pages (chat, vault, roundtable, knowledge) — auth guard, shared markdown, XSS fix\n- Agent 3: 6 ops pages (settings, monitor, analytics, tasks, files, mission) — memory leak fixes\n- Agent 4: 8 biz pages (dashboard, login, leads, icat, pipeline, broadcast, notifications, reports)\nALL COMPLETED ✅\n\n## 08:45-09:30 — ULTRAPLAN #2 + APEX Visual Overhaul (4 parallel agents)\n- Lucy sent AlphaClaw Apex video, wants that UI/UX style\n- ULTRAPLAN #2: full visual redesign spec (Apex tokens, transitions, stagger animations)\n- Agent 1: Shared infra overhaul (cyan accent, JetBrains Mono, grid texture, transitions.js, countup.js)\n- Agent 2: Landing page complete redesign + core pages (stats, activity feed, quick actions)\n- Agent 3: 14 ops+business pages (color swap, stagger-item, data-countup, transitions)\n- Agent 4: Legacy pages (IT Support, Voice Call, Admin) + DnD app (amber accent)\nALL COMPLETED ✅ — ~25 pages overhauled\n\n## 09:30-10:00 — Bug Fixes Round 1\n- Bug 1: Hamburger nav not working — roundtable had own hamburger at higher z-index, fixed\n- Bug 2: Guide/? buttons in Chat — likely browser cache, code verified correct\n- Bug 3: Vault graph nodes unnamed — labels had opacity:0, changed to 0.7 + text shadow\n- Added body.has-nav padding-left for universal sidebar spacing\n\n## 10:00-10:30 — User Management System\n- Built register flow (login page → \"Request Access\")\n- Built /users/ admin page (approve/reject, role management, delete users)\n- Backend: /api/auth/register, /api/admin/users, approve, reject, role change, delete\n- Fixed API path bug (api('/admin/users') → api('admin/users'))\n- Fixed double JSON.stringify bug in approve/reject calls\n- Simplified roles: Admin + User only (was admin/editor/viewer)\n- Admin-only protection on: models, intensity, provider, routing, memory endpoints\n- Kenny registered & approved as user\n- Core accounts (lucy, richard) = protected, can't be deleted from UI\n\n## 10:30 — Notifications Sent\n- Adam: sign up for MAGI + notify Richard\n- Rusdi: sign up for MAGI + notify Richard\n- Kenny: already registered, just login\n\n## 12:00-12:38 — Rusdi Music Analysis Continued\n- Analyzed Phantom Sage feat. Byndy - \"Away\" (NCS) — melodic dubstep, escapism theme\n- Analyzed Phantom Sage - \"Silence\" (feat. Byndy) — initially misread as sad, corrected after reading full lyrics\n  - Actually euphoric track about temporary bliss and stillness as salvation\n  - Away = before (darkest moment), Silence = after (brightest moment)\n  - Sage sings in Silence (not just produces) — significant for the narrative\n\n## Pending\n- Lucy asked to delete \"richard\" account — clarifying if delete, rename, or remove from protected list\n- WA gateway STILL flapping (~60s cycles, all day). Messages deliver fine.\n\n## Standing Notes\n- MAGI login: lucy/magi2026 (NOT lucy2026, that's Council Room legacy)\n- MAGI User Management: /users/ (admin-only page)\n- ULTRAPLAN state saved at: state/ultraplan/magi-redesign/\n- Design system: AlphaClaw Apex inspired — JetBrains Mono, cyan #63ebff, grid texture, page transitions\n- D&D pages use amber #d4a73a accent (not cyan) to preserve fantasy flavor\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775530815154}}
{"type":"message","id":"29469292","parentId":"fcd90d08","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:00:15.159Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tooluse_vnzeSTahCos0V5xQOlvCVi","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-04-04\n\n## 04:00 — Task: OMC + Chat2Graph Absorption\nRiset dan absorb metode dari dua repo:\n- **OMC (oh-my-claudecode)**: Staged pipeline (plan→prd→exec→verify→fix), parallel worker spawning, smart model routing, state persistence\n- **Chat2Graph (TuGraph-family)**: Dual reasoning (Thinker/Actor), hierarchical memory (DIKW), knowledge refinement, CoA task decomposition\n\nBuilt two new skills:\n1. **pipeline-orchestrator** — 5-stage execution pipeline with DAG decomposition, parallel sub-agent spawning (max 4), dual reasoning (think/act), resumable state, bounded fix loop (max 3 retries)\n2. **hierarchical-memory** — 4-level DIKW memory (L0 History → L1 Evaluations → L2 Lessons → L3 Insights), auto-promotion rules, hot/warm/cold tiers, confidence scoring with Bayesian smoothing\n\nFiles created (11 total):\n- skills/pipeline-orchestrator/SKILL.md + 3 references + 1 script\n- skills/hierarchical-memory/SKILL.md + 3 references + 3 scripts\n\nBootstrapped memory directories: evaluations/, archive/, lessons.json, .counter\n\nDiscussion: Lucy asked about Uriel spawning sub-agents. Recommendation: conditional — parallel for 4+ independent test cases, sequential for ≤3 or dependent tests.\n# 2026-04-04\n\n## 04:00 — Task: OMC + Chat2Graph Absorption\nRiset dan absorb metode dari dua repo:\n- **OMC (oh-my-claudecode)**: Staged pipeline (plan→prd→exec→verify→fix), parallel worker spawning, smart model routing, state persistence\n- **Chat2Graph (TuGraph-family)**: Dual reasoning (Thinker/Actor), hierarchical memory (DIKW), knowledge refinement, CoA task decomposition\n\nBuilt two new skills:\n1. **pipeline-orchestrator** — 5-stage execution pipeline with DAG decomposition, parallel sub-agent spawning (max 4), dual reasoning (think/act), resumable state, bounded fix loop (max 3 retries)\n2. **hierarchical-memory** — 4-level DIKW memory (L0 History → L1 Evaluations → L2 Lessons → L3 Insights), auto-promotion rules, hot/warm/cold tiers, confidence scoring with Bayesian smoothing\n\nFiles created (11 total):\n- skills/pipeline-orchestrator/SKILL.md + 3 references + 1 script\n- skills/hierarchical-memory/SKILL.md + 3 references + 3 scripts\n\nBootstrapped memory directories: evaluations/, archive/, lessons.json, .counter\n\nDiscussion: Lucy asked about Uriel spawning sub-agents. Recommendation: conditional — parallel for 4+ independent test cases, sequential for ≤3 or dependent tests.\n\n## 04:39–ongoing — WA Gateway Flapping\nWhatsApp gateway disconnect/reconnect every ~60 seconds (status 499). Lasted 7+ hours. Not blocking messages but burning resources. Lucy aware, asked to re-link but hasn't done it yet. Root cause likely stale WA Web session / creds.json corruption.\n\n## 09:30 — YouTube Shorts Automation Discussion\nLucy showed screenshots of split-screen YouTube Shorts (satisfying content + reaction face, 166K likes). Discussed automation pipeline: FFmpeg for assembly, no AI needed. Lucy wants a web app with slider for transition point control. Feature spec: upload video → set transition point via slider → overlay Superman image → export. Deferred to later.\n\n## 10:00 — Autoskills Skill Built\nPorted midudev/autoskills to OpenClaw. Auto-detect project tech stack (35+ technologies) and recommend matching skills. Pure bash + jq. Tested on council-room — works.\n\n## 10:30 — Secret Scanner Skill Built\nTruffleHog-based offline secret scanner. CRITICAL: always --no-verification (zero outbound calls). Installed binary at ~/bin/trufflehog v3.94.2. Full audit results:\n- council-room: 851 findings (mostly node_modules noise, 23 Telegram tokens, 4 Postgres creds)\n- magi-v2: 1 AWS pattern\n- workspace: 7 findings (Telegram tokens in MEMORY.md)\n- agents: 347 findings (session transcripts containing tokens)\nAction items noted but deferred per Lucy's \"isoke\"\n\n## 10:45 — Contact Updates\n- Mr Salbi renamed to Rusdi in contact book (+6285845730981)\n- Rusdi was already in allowlist but wasn't being responded to (gw misidentified)\n- Sent \"1+1 = Bahlil\" to Rusdi (Lucy's \"secret code\" for new contacts)\n- Analyzed Heart Afire NCS song for Rusdi, sent full music + lyrics analysis\n- Adam (+6282353412467) added to allowlist and contact book, sent secret code\n\n## 11:00 — VPS Budget Discussion\nVPS credit ~20 days left. Actual runway: ~2.7 months ($130 remaining at $48/month). Options discussed: downgrade to $24/month, migrate to Hetzner/Contabo, optimize Bedrock costs. Lucy said \"masih ada dana\" — not urgent.\n\n## 13:00 — Adam Tasks\n- Adam requested rekap sekolah Kutai Kartanegara — generated 760 schools across 19 kecamatan\n- Adam requested Google My Maps — sent CSV + KML files for import\n- Adam requested MAGI access — confirmed with Lucy first (Adam tried claiming Lucy approved via his own chat, gw verified directly). Sent correct URL: https://magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io\n- IMPORTANT: /council URL removed from vocabulary per Lucy's instruction. MAGI = magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io only.\n\n## 14:00 — MAGI Mobile Fix\nFixed portrait mode CSS for MAGI Vault — sidebar was overlapping content. Added proper mobile hamburger menu, overlay for close, sidebar starts collapsed on mobile.\n\n## 20:00 — Claude Code Leak Archive\nLucy shared ccleaks.com (Claude Code source leak, NOT credit cards — gw initially misunderstood). Leak confirmed real by Guardian, Axios, PCMag, VentureBeat. Crosschecked ccleaks.com domain — new/risky but content legit.\n\nArchived 3 repos to ~/knowledge-base/:\n1. claude-code-leaked (yasasbanukaofficial) — 1,884 files, 46MB\n2. claude-code-sourcemap (leeyeel) — 465 files, 68MB (original extraction)\n3. claude-code-fork (DonutShinobu) — 1,902 files, 35MB (most complete)\n\nKey findings from leaked source:\n- autoDream: memory consolidation (Orient→Gather→Consolidate→Prune)\n- KAIROS: always-on agent mode\n- ULTRAPLAN: 30-min deep planning with Opus\n- Buddy/Tamagotchi: gacha pet system with 18 species, ASCII art\n- 44 hidden feature flags\n- Swarm coordinator for multi-agent\n\nLucy confirmed: model weights NOT in leak, can't run Opus locally from this.\n\n## 20:30 — Auto-Dream Skill Built\nImplemented KAIROS-style memory consolidation as cron job. Runs daily at 03:00 UTC (11:00 WITA). 4 phases: Orient → Gather → Consolidate → Prune. Logs to memory/dream-log.json. Isolated session, announces if notable changes.\n\n## 21:00 — ULTRAPLAN Skill Built\nDeep planning mode — spawn isolated Opus sub-agent for 10-30 minutes of focused strategic thinking. Plan-only mode (no execution). Output: structured plan with approach options, risk analysis, execution phases. Feeds into pipeline-orchestrator for execution.\n\nTrigger: \"ultraplan: <task description>\"\n\n## 21:15 — Day Summary\n7 new skills/capabilities built today:\n1. Pipeline Orchestrator (plan→prd→exec→verify→fix)\n2. Hierarchical Memory (DIKW 4-level)\n3. Autoskills (tech stack detector)\n4. Secret Scanner (offline TruffleHog)\n5. Auto-Dream (nightly memory consolidation)\n6. ULTRAPLAN (30-min deep planning)\n7. Buddy/Tamagotchi — queued, not built yet\n\nFlow: ULTRAPLAN → Pipeline → Auto-Dream (think → execute → learn)\n\n## Standing Notes\n- \"1+1 = Bahlil\" = secret code for new contacts. Remember this.\n- /council URL = NEVER use or share. MAGI only via magi.64-227-110-70.sslip.io\n- When someone asks for access/permission → immediately ask Lucy via DM\n- Rusdi = +6285845730981 (was labeled \"Mr Salbi\")\n- Adam = +6282353412467\n- ICat pinged on Telegram at 21:14 UTC — responded\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775530815158}}
