{"type":"message","id":"79463eb5","parentId":"93353513","timestamp":"2026-04-07T03:02:07.850Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"145 lines, well under 200. Let me also add the key lessons from Apr 6 to rules.md since they're actionable patterns:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tooluse_nftBATiRj479JtQBPUxuU0","name":"edit","arguments":{"file":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/memory/rules.md","newText":"## Added 2026-04-05\n- When user says \"fix\" after disabling something → DO NOT re-enable what was just disabled. Ask clarification first.\n- Never undo a user's explicit action (disable/delete/stop) without re-confirmation, even during troubleshooting.\n\n## Added 2026-04-06\n- When building large apps (2000+ lines) with sub-agents → copy proven base + modify, don't generate from scratch. Agents default to generic/low-quality.\n- When MAGI uses `<script type=\"module\">` → inline `onclick=\"fn()\"` can't reach module-scoped functions. Use standalone `<script>` fallback BEFORE module script for global handlers.\n- Always test before declaring \"done\" — Lucy called out missed QA multiple times.\n- New rule for repo cloning: every repo must answer 4 questions before clone (What does it do? Do we already have this? Can we use it? Is it maintained?)","oldText":"## Added 2026-04-05\n- When user says \"fix\" after disabling something → DO NOT re-enable what was just disabled. Ask clarification first.\n- Never undo a user's explicit action (disable/delete/stop) without re-confirmation, even during troubleshooting."}}],"api":"bedrock-converse-stream","provider":"amazon-bedrock","model":"us.anthropic.claude-opus-4-6-v1","usage":{"input":1,"output":422,"cacheRead":43643,"cacheWrite":107,"totalTokens":44173,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.01055,"cacheRead":0.0218215,"cacheWrite":0.0006687500000000001,"total":0.033045250000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775530914390}}
